<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><title>Amazing grace</title>
<key>D</key>
<lyrics>[V1]
 Å nåde stor og underfull,
 som fant meg i min synd.
 Så svak jeg var,
 men ved Guds Ord,
 jeg ser som før var blind.

[V2]
 Guds nåde tok
 den angsten bort,
 som synden hadde skapt.
 Hvor det var rikt,
 hvor det var stort,
 for meg som var fortapt.

[V3]
 Jeg glemmer aldri
 første gang,
 da jeg fikk vende om.
 Da brøt den nye
 sangen frem,
 da jeg til troen kom.

[V4]
 Min lenke brast
 Jeg ble satt fri
 Min Gud, Min frelser løste meg
 En flod av nåde strømmer ned
 Å nåde stor
 Hans kjærlighet

[V5]
 Amazing grace!
 How sweet the sound,
 That saved a wretch like me!
 I once was lost,
 but now I'm found,
 Was blind, but now I see.

[V6]
 'Twas grace that taught
 my heart to fear,
 And grace my fears relieved;
 How precious did
 that grace appear
 The hour I first believed;

[V7]
 Thro' many dangers,
 toils and snares,
 I have already come;
 'Tis grace hath brought
 me safe thus far,
 And grace will
 lead me home.

[V8]
 The Lord has promised
 good to me,
 His Word my hope secures;
 He will my shield
 and portion be,
 As long as life endures.

[V9]
 Yea, when this flesh
 and heart shall fail,
 And mortal life shall cease,
 I shall possess,
 within the veil,
 A life of joy and peace.

[V10]
 The world shall
 soon to ruin go,
 The sun refuse to shine;
 But God, who called
 me here below,
 Shall be forever mine.

[V11]
 When we've been
 there ten thousand years,
 Bright shining as the sun,
 We've no less days
 to sing God's praise
 Than when we first begun.

[V12]
 Praise God, Praise God
 Praise God, Praise God
 Praise God, Praise God,
 Praise God.
 Praise God, Praise God
 Praise God, Praise God
 Praise God, Praise God,
 Praise God.

[V13]
 Amen, Amen, Amen, Amen
 Amen, Amen, Amen.
 Amen, Amen, Amen, Amen
 Amen, Amen, Amen.

[V14]
 Min lenke brast
 Jeg ble satt fri
 Min Gud, Min frelser løste meg
 En flod av nåde strømmer ned
 Å nåde stor
 Hans kjærlighet

[V15]
 My chains are gone
 I've been set free
 My God My savior ransomed me
 And like a flood his mercy rains
 Unending love
 Amazing grace

[V16]
 The Lord has promised good to me
 His Word my hope secures
 He will my Shield
 And portion be
 As long as life endures

[V17]
 The earth shall soon
 Desolve like snow
 The sun refuse to shine
 But God who called me here below
 Will be forever mine
 Will be forever mine
 You are forever mine</lyrics>
<aka>Å nåde stor og underfull</aka>
<presentation>v1 v2 v3 v4 v5 v6 v7 v8 v9 v10 v11 v12 v13 v14 v15 v16 v17</presentation>
</song>